Ӯ[{"URL":"/image/c18cf4186c974bafbf860e7a1142954297fa631c","importURL":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/96147277@N00/4499575982","licence":"CC BY-NC-SA 2.0","media_type":"inscription","sha1":"c18cf4186c974bafbf860e7a1142954297fa631c","width":1024,"height":768}]"Ҷ
ғJulia
For all the wonderful times we have enjoyed in London
and to many more years of life, love and happiness.
Ross - June 2006"Ү
„Cecilia Vajda
Professor, Liszt Academy of Music, Budapest
Direcot of the Hungarian Radio Choir
Britain's leading 'KodГЎly' expert"Ү
„For Jack Hutton
A very special man, editor and Jazzman, who
always had a place in his heart for those
less fortunate than himself"Ү
„In loving memory of my dearest father . Sudir Sareen.
who enjoyed spending time with his famly in this Park. With all my love Parul"ү
ҶIn loving memory of Robert Patrick Le Marchand
15th June 1976 - 24th November 2014
Close your eyes. Fall in love. Stay there. - Rumi"ү
ҶMary Beverley (1913- 2008) and Eric Beverley (1917 -1980)
Long time residents of Marylebone
and members of the St Marylebone Society"Ҡ
ҮIN GRATEFUL THANKS FOR
MANY HOURS OF PEACE AND TRANQUILITY
ENJOYED IN THESE LOVELY GARDENS
HELEN AND KENNETH MURPHY
TORONTO, CANADA"Ӣ
ҲFOR CHARLES E OSTHIMER III
IN HONOUR OF HIS BIRTHDAY
7 MAY 1990
LOVINGLY DONATED BY HIS FAMILY
"BECAUSE HE LOVES THIS SPECIAL PLACE""Қ
ҠFor Dan R. Cullum
For giving us a love of London, this Garden and
for the many cherished family memories.
From Karen, Monece and Nicole"Һ
ӢDedicated to
Adrian Newman
Who spent much time enjoying these gardens
From his friends and colleagues at
Richard Ellis and 3B Technical"Ҹ
ҢIn memory of our beloved mother
Beata Tarnowska-Nabghali
Who loved the beauty of Berkeley Square Gardens
From Nevin, Khaled, Assem & Omar"‘
ҺPresented by friends in memory  of Ronnie Shaw-Kennedy. M.B.E.
Resident of Mount Street and member of Westminster City Council from 1953-1972"’
ҸJohn Roche
Who spent many moments of tranquil contemplation
of this beautiful square and his lovely daughter Pearl
Both so dear to his heart"’
ҸPresented by an American Melvin Bloom
who hopes all who sit here
will feel the magic of this beautiful place
and the song of the nightingale"–
“In Honour of Christiane Mambrino
Daughter of the General Manager of Claridges
She used to walk in this square
with her little sister and brother"—
”In loving memory of
Peter Lance Penco, 1959 (Trinidad) - 2008 (Kenya)
Who spent many happy years here
and gave us so much joy, love and laughter."—
”SEYMOUR AUGENBRAUN - A NEW YORKER
AND ARTIST FOR WHOM THIS SPOT IN LONDON IS HIS OASIS OF BEAUTY
FROM HIS WIFE ARLENE AND FAMILY ON JULY 15TH 1986"ӣ
ҳYoung Lovers seek perfection.
Old lovers learn the art of sewing shreds together.
And of seeing beauty in a multiplicity of patches
PRC to LMC - 1996"һ
ӣRemembering the wonderful
Des Williams
Who brought street dance to our Saturday classes in 1993
Teaching our students with energy and skill for 25 years"Ө
Ў"fair Quiet, have I found thee here" (MARVELL)
"a garden is a lovesome thing" (BROWN)
Given by Bobbe & Myles Wilder
Temecula, California 1996 40th Anniversary"§
