ҪTo honour
Thomas J. Johnston of San Francisco
Who visited these gardens as a Commander in the
US Navy during the Normandy Landings and
later with his family and President of his company"Ж
ГTo honour
Thomas J. Johnston
Of San Francisco
Who visited these gardens as a commander in the U.S. Navy
During the Normandy Landings and Later with his family
and as president of his company"И
Е"Here with a Loaf of Bread beneath the Bough,
A Flask of Wine, a Book of Verse вҖ” and Thou
Beside me singing in the Wilderness вҖ”
And Wilderness is Paradise enow."
RubГЎiyГЎt of Omar KhayyГЎm"О
ЛThis Bench and the Golden Roses planted either side of
the Gardener's Hut are to commemorate the work of
JOHN SPEED
the Gardener in Golden Square and
Leicester Square Gardens who died in October 2002"П
МIN TREASURED MEMORY OF MY DARLING HUSBAND
FRANIE DANIELS 25.10.1910 - 15.2.1992
HIS BUSINESS WAS IN MOUNT STREET
TOGETHER WE SHARED THIS SECRET GARDEN
FOR EVER AND ALWAYS AND ALL ETERNITY YOUR SHELAGH"Ц
УTo JAN CLEMINSON (nee HOLLAND) ARCM 1919-2009
